    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>When a microbot grenade detonates, the blast radius fills with microbots like those created by the microbot assault spell. The microbots consider only creatures in the blast radius to be the thrower&rsquo;s enemies, and they do not discriminate between the thrower&rsquo;s allies and enemies. The microbots last for 3 rounds. More advanced grenades create more dangerous microbots. The first time a creature leaves the area of the microbot cloud during a round, that creature takes an amount of magical piercing damage according to the grenade&rsquo;s type.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mk 1 (Level 6):</strong>&nbsp;1d6</li>\n<li><strong>Mk 2 (Level 9):</strong>&nbsp;2d6</li>\n<li><strong>Mk 3 (Level 12):</strong>&nbsp;3d6</li>\n<li><strong>Mk 4 (Level 15):</strong>&nbsp;3d10</li>\n<li><strong>Mk 5 (Level 18):&nbsp;</strong>4d12</li>\n</ul>"
    },
